y«/b»\nRobert de Comyn is thought to have originally come from Flanders and been one of the Conqueror's companions. His parentage is unknown. In 1069 he was made earl of Northumberland, and when he attempted to claim his lands he and all his men were slain at Durham on 28 January 1069/70.\n\nAlthough the name of his wife is not known, he is believed to have had two sons:\n\n1.) John de Comyn\n\n2.) William de Comyn, Chancellor of Scotland","sourceList":[{"title":"Robert de Comyn, \"Find A Grave Index\"","sourceType":"FSREADONLY","sourceLink":"https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:6ZRS-B93D","sourceUri":"QVSL-VB5"},{"title":"Wikipedia","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_de_Comines","sourceUri":"914H-WN4"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"1","year":"1020","date":"about 1020","place":"Conteville, Calvados, Normandy, France"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1021","date":"circa 1021","place":"Altyre, Morayshire, Scotland","age":"1","id":"GLZJ-JXG"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1053","date":"1053","place":"Altyre, Morayshire, Scotland","age":"33","id":"GVWB-8M7"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1053","date":"about 1053","place":"Morayshire, Scotland","age":"33","id":"L58D-D63"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1060","date":"about 1060","place":"Argyll, Scotland","age":"40","id":"LVZV-HS7"},{"name":"TitleOfNobility","sources":"0","year":"1068","date":"1068–28 January 1069","age":"49"},{"name":"Cause of death","sources":"0","year":"1069","date":"28 January 1069","type":"USER_DEFINED","age":"49"},{"name":"Death","sources":"1","year":"1069","date":"28 January 1069","place":"Durham, Northumberland, England","age":"49"}],"parent":[{"name":"John De Tynedale, De Comyn","gender":"Male","lifespan":"0991–1021","birthDate":"A+0991","deathDate":"A+1021","age":30,"@type":"Person","identifier":"GLZJ-JXG","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GLZJ-JXG/john-de-tynedale%2C-d